The paper focuses on the use of Generative Adversarial Networks (GANs) for image generation, specifically for faces. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also proposes a new regularizer for GANs and a cascaded framework for combining GANs, which involves machine learning techniques such as feature matching and adversarial training, indicating a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions applications in movies and video games, which suggests a potential focus on graphics (cs.GR) and multimedia (cs.MM).
